definitions.definition: That which clinches ; that which makes something final or firm ; a decisive factor.
examples: The clincher was that we couldn't wait any longer to leave, or it would get dark.

definitions.definition: A tyre with a bead around the edge to attach to the rim of the wheel when inflated .

main_definition: That which clinches ; that which makes something final or firm ; a decisive factor.
